'''Andrzej Ajnenkiel''' (21 February 1931 – 10 April 2015) was a [[Poland|Polish]] historian. He specialized in the political history of Poland and the history of Polish law, especially [[constitutional law]].
From 1949 to 1954 Ajnenkiel studied law at the [[University of Warsaw]]. Since 1979 Ajnenkiel had been a professor at the Institute of History at the [[Polish Academy of Sciences]] in Warsaw. In 1991 he gained a professor degree, the highest academic degree in Poland, and later a [[habilitation]]. He was a member and director of several historical societies, including the [[Polish Historical Society (Poland)|Polish Historical Society]].
==Works== * ''Historia ustroju Polski 1764-1939'' (1969) * ''Administracja w Polsce: zarys historyczny'' (Administration in Poland: Historical Overview) (1975) * ''Parlamentaryzm II Rzeczypospolitej'' (1975) * ''Od rządów ludowych do przewrotu majowego: zarys dziejów politycznych Polski 1918-1926'' (1977) * ''Polska po przewrocie majowym: zarys dziejów politycznych Polski 1926-1939'' (Poland after the May Coup: Overview of the Political History of Poland 1926-1939) (1980) * ''Polskie konstytucje'' (Polish Constitutions) (1991) * ''Prezydenci Polski'' (Presidents of Poland) (1991) * ''Konstytucje Polski w rozwoju dziejowym 1791-1997'' (2001)
