'''Michael Denis Biddiss''' (born 1942) is emeritus professor of history at the University of Reading. He specialises in the history of the development of [[Racism|racist ideology]], and the [[history of medicine]].

==Early life==
Michael Denis Biddiss was born in 1942.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n79007064/ Biddiss, Michael D. (Michael Denis) 1942-.] World Cat. Retrieved 6 December 2015.</ref>

==Career==
Biddiss was formerly with [[Downing College, Cambridge|Downing College]], University of Cambridge. He has been professor of history at the [[University of Reading]] since 1979 (emeritus since 2004), and was dean of letters and social sciences from 1982 to 1985. He was president of the [[Historical Association]] from 1991 to 1994.<ref>[https://www.reading.ac.uk/history/about/staff/M-Biddiss.aspx Staff Profile:Professor Michael Biddiss.] University of Reading. Retrieved 6 December 2015.</ref> He specialises in the history of the development of racist ideology.

==Selected publications==
* ''The age of the masses: Ideas and society in Europe since 1870''. Penguin, 1977. {{ISBN|0140219870}} 
* ''Father of racist ideology: The social and political thought of Count Gobineau''. [[Weybright & Talley]], New York, 1970. {{ISBN|0297000853}}<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/2776889 Reviewed Work: ''Father of Racist Ideology: The Social and Political Thought of Count Gobineau''. by Michael D. Biddiss Review by: George W. Stocking, Jr. [[American Journal of Sociology]] Vol. 77, No. 2 (Sep., 1971), pp. 349-351.] Retrieved 6 December 2015.</ref>
* ''Gobineau: Selected political writings''. [[Jonathan Cape]], London, 1970. (Editor and introduction) ([[Roots of the Right]] series) {{ISBN|0224617273}}
* ''Thatcherism: Personality and politics''. [[Macmillan Publishers|Macmillan]], Basingstoke, 1987. (Edited with	[[Kenneth Minogue|Kenneth R. Minogue]]) {{ISBN|0333447247}}
* ''Images of race''. [[Leicester University Press]], Leicester, 1979. (Editor) {{ISBN|0718550609}}
* ''The uses and abuses of antiquity''. [[Peter Lang (publisher)|Peter Lang]], 1999. (Editor with [[Maria Wyke]]) {{ISBN|3906761649}}
* ''Themes in modern European history, 1890-1945''. Routledge, 2009. (Edited with [[Nicholas Atkin]])
* ''The Wiley-Blackwell dictionary of modern European history since 1789''. Wiley-Blackwell, 2011. (Edited with Nicholas Atkin and [[Frank Tallett]])

